<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I'll believe it when i see it, but this is what I know so far:<P>Aug 2nd, 1999: VZ goes live, 2nd team server to go up at the relatively same time.<P>March 2001: Major PvP changes announce, supposedly focused on X-teaming and Deleveling.<P><BR>In about a 2 year period this is what has been changed in PvP and more specifically VZ.<P>- Nerf on spell damage from 100% to 66%<BR>- Removal of Charm and Fear spells/songs in PvP<BR>- Initially you could loot melee primary/secondary slot items, they changed it to just all other equippable slots except those.<BR>- Changed from Coin+1 to just Coin.<BR>- Addressed perma-mezzing<BR>- Just recently nerfed the SK HT Disc<BR>- Changed SK HT from resetting on death to prevent drive by HT's.<P>(I know I'm missing a couple here, but those are some of the more major ones)<P>There have been some other changes to PvE and class boosts in skills, disciplines, and spells (IE. addition of some of these things when Kunark and Velious came out that effect PvP in the long run) Some of these include the addition of unresistable spells (Winged Death, Splurt, etc), others included the dics.<P>In all this time nothing has ever been adressed concerning either X-teaming or Deleveling.<P>There have been several crusades to adress these facts, but many times we had Abashi (pre-absor) comment that VI would never hinder friends from opposite teams from grouping if they so desired. 3-team x-teaming seems to be accepted as the "light" team, where as 4-team x-teaming is seen as the devil itself.<P>Now, if they are going to do anything concerning x-teaming, its going to affect all teams regardless if you are a "light team" member and want to make "alliances and fun stuff" or a evil 4 team "X-teamer".<P>IMO this could potentially solve some things. <P>Going FFA I don't think is the answer though if thats what they are considering. <P>The teams were a wonderful "concept" but the implementation of it and VI's subsequent lack of any feedback and proactive involvement to solve the major problems with the teams has turned it into a lost cause. The major problems with x-teaming seem to be Immortal Healing and Immortal Scouting. Ignore the fact that it goes against "Server Dynamics" or Verant's intention for "Teams", because the moment the 1st "Light" teams decided to get together and not screw up there faction was the day it started going downhill.<P>If VI is considering going FFA instead of teams, then that would techniqually solve those problems. They're wouldn't be teams, anyone could group with anyone, no x-teamers, no immortal healing, no immortal scouting. Poof we're Rallos (nothing against RZ, but the people who wanted to do FFA went red, the ones who liked the team concept went Teams). If thats the case it's going to be a culture shock to quite a bit of people who actually choose to single team and have always done so. Single team, you don't have to worry about accidentally AE'ing your group, mezzing them, etc. FFA we'll make quite a bit of people have to learn to play a different way. That may be good, it may be bad. It's all specualtion anyways since FFA is just the rumor at the moment.<P>IMO as long as they have faction hits I think a lot of people will remain true to the Light/Dark concept, whether we go FFA or not. An elf isn't going to pk a "human team" member if it may ruin his/her faction and they might not be able to bank in FP or Queynos. /shudder<P><BR>I'm primarily ranting here since I'm eternally pessimistic when Verant decides to get off their high horse, get away from designing new lands and new l00t, and ignore the problems with their existing desings, and "fix" something that has been the source of complaints and concerns for near 2 years. Regardless, I'm afraid of this patch or "fix" more then any other "fix" that has been done. <P>My 2cps dished out and thrown wildly and erratically.<P>Sinklar
</FONT>
