REAL SOLUTION - <P>Not everyone will be happy if you hardcode the teams.  Not everyone is happy now with all the x teaming (and healers and buffers they can't touch!!).  How do you make most everyone happy in this situation?<P>This will require some work on your part Verant, but I think it's well worth the investment in keeping PvP alive.<P>What needs to happen: Three servers set up for PvP.  One is hardcoded Good Vs Evil.  Alot of players like teams this way.  This would prevent x teaming from good to evil, but allow all "good" aligned races to team together.  Another server is hardcoded 4 teams.  No x team healing or buffing whatsoever.  Current PvP teams server players are given the option to movelog to the server of their choice - G vs E, 4 teams, or Rallos Zek (x team all you want here).<P>This would satisfy most everyone's playing style and allow the heinous x teaming to be combated by those who like to roleplay.<BR>
