Delevelers: Can be a decent problem, but heck, so can that ogre SK with a Runic Carver and 100+ on all resists at level 4.  I dont think it's enough of a problem to worry about.<P>Cross-Teaming: The majority of the people dont want cross-teaming removed.  Why fix something that people dont consider broken?<P>The real issue of PvP is the ability for everyone to participate in it.  If you chose to play one of the support classes (Bard, Enchanter, Cleric) on PvP, you are giving in to the fact that you will have a hard team beating blues that know what they are doing.  These classes aren't meant to do damage in PvE.  Thats understood.  They can have different roles and still participate.  But 80% of PvP is forced solo'ing, so how are they supposed to do damage when they aren't built for it?<P>Or take tanks at around 10-30.  They are completely helpless to the wizard who just roots and nukes.  No way to combat that besides hoping you can keep up with the lag and continue interupting (although especially in high 20s unless you can get a good bash off every time they will channel).  Above 30 tanks start getting good resist gear to let them take the casters, but rarely can a warrior take out an even wizard if the warrior is using standard equip for their level.<P>These are the kind of changes that need to be made, making PvP viable for all classes, and knowing that if you dont make a wizard or mage that you are at a distinct disadvantage in PvP.
