<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Remove Deleveling!<P><BR>As hard as the game can be, deleveling is just demoralizing. One false move from either you or a group member and you lose a level in certain cases. <P>1. we are penalized after lvl 6+ for dying loss of exp or a lvl if you just got there.<BR>2. After lvl 20 is you want to lvl grouping is the key, with the exception of druids until much higher lvls, when killing really uber npc you need well organized armadas, which are hard to come by on PvP servers with the large amount of hostility.<BR>3. Then at 30 you add hell lvls. As well they only get harder and then at 50 + it's all HELL.<BR>4.Melee characters have to troop to find their corpses and may spend an entire game night trying to get it. Since their equipment is on they're body, making them weaker than when they lost they're body to an NPC or a PC. Only now having to return to that same area defensless, and the NPC full health. (bad situation)<P>IMO all the above is fine on a regular server and but some of it is just not suitable for PvP. The idea of grouping as you get higher is a great idea as you get further through the game. It builds friends as well as a more diverse gamer and game character. Hell lvls are fine, all games should get harder as they go on, it's called challenge and getting through it is an accomplishment. The corpse runs are ok as well, you should have a group or friends from playing that will assist you. I have no problems if someone attcks me and loots me or if i need to defend myself, attacking another player. As well the occasional "I'm bored let's go kill some unsuspecting player. Ganking is part of the game for pkers (it may suck) but you should always be prepared.<P>My issue is when you see a player being malicously EXPed that's just not cool. That aspect of the game should not be an option for another player or a consequence that other players can facilitate. If these problems can't be enforced then there should be a remedy put in place that would substitute for the inability of monitoring incidents suck as EXPing other players.<P><BR>IMO exp loss is ok, but with everything working against you lossing a lvl isn't cool.<BR>you should only loss exp with in the lvl you are in and if you jsut got there, you should just stay with in that lvl, or if you want to add another challenge make a red line that adds up which would be like a negative within that lvl , without losing that lvl.<P>This would keep players from deleveling as well as punish players who would be foolish enought to try deleving after this was implemented, as well as keeping the challenge to regular gamers, to not die and play smart. Also it wouldn't be as bad for people who were getting EXPed by other malicous players. And if ppl were complaining still just don't add the negative exp for dying once a new lvl is gained just leave them at zero. Although i think losing exp within a lvl should still be implemented if you in the positive. <P>
</FONT>
